# Agent procedure layer — AUTHORED markdown, not generated code.
# 343 of the repo's 648 Prettier offenders (53%) live here. Prettier's Markdown
# printer would reflow prose, tables and code fences across every skill purely to
# satisfy a formatter that has never run on them — churn with no reader benefit,
# and it would fight the .agents -> .claude/skills symlink invariant that
# adapter-sync-check guards. Skills are edited as prose; leave them as written.
# (.claude/skills is a symlink INTO this directory, so one rule covers both.)
.agents/skills/

# ALL authored Markdown — the rule above, generalised once we measured it.
# Prettier earns its keep on CODE, where it ends bikeshedding in review and makes
# diffs mean something. On hand-written prose it earns nothing here: formatting
# docs/ + the root .md files produced 3,758 changed lines, of which ~1,847 were
# table-pipe padding and ~1,618 were *emphasis* -> _emphasis_. Both render
# IDENTICALLY. That is a large diff across the architecture docs, buying a
# rendered output nobody can tell apart, while burying real edits in noise and
# conflicting with any in-flight doc branch.
#
# So the ruling is: Prettier formats code, not prose. Markdown is reviewed by
# reading it. Removing this line is a decision to accept the churn above — it is
# not a bug fix.
**/*.md
